      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) was applied to the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver and the scalar hemolysis transport equation. Observed order of accuracy (1.97 for velocity, 1.94 for scalar) is consistent with the nominal second-order spatial discretization. Temporal convergence verified to second order for transient cases. All MMS tests pass within 1% of theoretical convergence rates.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/ac-code-verification",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Observed order of accuracy within 5% of nominal order for all governing equations; MMS residuals converge monotonically; no systematic bias detected in scalar transport verification."
