      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study performed across three grids (coarse 2.1M, medium 5.8M, fine 14.2M cells) following ASME V&V 20 GCI methodology. Grid convergence index (GCI) for NIH at the design operating point: GCI_fine = 2.3%, GCI_medium = 6.1%. Richardson extrapolation applied; asymptotic convergence confirmed (GCI ratio 0.98). The fine mesh is used for all production runs.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
