      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions are documented with traceability to NIST-calibrated instrumentation. Flow rate controlled to ±0.05 L/min (Coriolis meter, NIST-traceable calibration); rotational speed to ±5 RPM (optical encoder); fluid temperature to ±0.2 °C. Hematocrit measured pre- and post-test; variation < 1.5% across test series. Environmental conditions (temperature, humidity) logged and within specified bounds throughout testing.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
