      "rationale": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) is directly specified in the COU as the hemolysis acceptance metric. Secondary QoIs (velocity field, pressure head) are mechanistically linked to NIH through the power-law hemolysis model and serve as intermediate validation anchors. The mapping from simulation output to regulatory decision quantity is documented in the QoI traceability matrix. No surrogate QoIs are used without documented justification.",
